</div>
<div class="col-lg-6">
    <h3>Classes</h3>
    <div class="panel-group" id="classes">
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#classes" href="#addclass">How do I add a Class?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="addclass" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            Go to the Manage School page under My Teacher Profile in the upper right (you must be a Teacher or Owner to add classes and you must first have a School set up)
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            On the Class panel, click the Add Class link
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#classes" href="#importclass">How do import classes from Facebook?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="importclass" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            First, you must be logged in through Facebook, not email registration.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Click on a school under My Teacher Profile
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            In the classes section, click the Add Class button
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            On the first screen, pick Import from Facebook button
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            The wizard will walk you through importing the event.  You’ll have to verify the information, name, date/time, etc.  And you’ll have to specify additional information – skill level, dance styles, location, etc.
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#classes" href="#addclassstyles">How do I add dance styles for my Class?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="addclassstyles" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            If you need to add/change the dance styles for your event, go to your School page under My Teacher Profile
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Then, select the Class in the Classes section
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Go to the Dance Styles section and either add or delete Styles
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#classes" href="#addclassplaylist">How do I add YouTube playlists to my Class?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="addclassplaylist" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            You’ll need a YouTube account and can either import single YouTube videos or full YouTube playlists
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Add a Playlist in YouTube (be sure to set the default upload as “unlisted” in the YouTube settings).
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Copy the “share link” from the YouTube playlist.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Go to the Manage Class page under your Manage School page
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Go to the Videos section and paste the YouTube playlist link and click import
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#classes" href="#addclassvideo">How do I add YouTube videos to my Class?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="addclassvideo" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            You’ll need a YouTube account and can either import single YouTube videos or full YouTube playlists
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Add a Video in YouTube (be sure to set the default upload as “unlisted” in the YouTube settings).
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Copy the “share link” from the YouTube video.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Go to the Manage Class page under your Manage School page
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Go to the Videos section and paste the YouTube video link and click import
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#classes" href="#addclassalbum">How do I import a Facebook Album to my Class?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="addclassalbum" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            Go to the Manage Class page
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Go to the Pictures section
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Either click the Add Facebook Album button to select one of your albums or copy and paste the album url link in the Add Album box and import
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#classes" href="#addclasspicture">How do I import a Facebook Picture to my Class?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="addclasspicture" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            Go to the Manage Class page
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Go to the Pictures section
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Copy and paste the picture url link in the Add Picture box and import
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#classes" href="#addclassfacebookobject">How do I attach Facebook Pages/Groups/Events to my Class?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="addclassfacebookobject" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            Go to the Manage Class page
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Scroll down to the “Connect” section
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Copy and paste the url link of your Facebook Page/Group/Event and click the Add Linked Media button.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            All status updates to your Facebook object will now show in your Class
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="panel panel-default">
            <div class="panel-heading">
                <h4 class="panel-title">
                    <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#socials" href="#addclassteachers">How do I add Teachers for my Class?</a>
                </h4>
            </div>
            <div id="addclassteachers" class="panel-collapse collapse">
                <div class="panel-body">
                    <ol>
                        <li>
                            Click the School in the upper right menu
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Find the Class in the Classes section and click the link
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Scroll down to the "Teachers" section
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Type in the name of the Teacher, click the matching name and click Add
                        </li>
                    </ol>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
